CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 2, 1961, pg. 25 reads: "Kick-Off Meeting - Young people of the Allegheny Union Baptist Association held their kick-off meeting on Aug. 25 in the home of Mrs. Ruth West, youth adviser. Left to right, seated: Patricia Johnson, secretary; Cynthia Roberts, Kiski Area president; Mrs. Ruth West, adviser; Arlene Jones, Pittsburgh Area president, and Joan Purifoy, Lower Monongahela president.  Standing: Marion Thompson, president; Wayne Holt, financial secretary, and Louise Wingfield, pianist.  The Rev. W.D. Petett is Moderator. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left, seated: Patricia Johnson, Cynthia Roberts, Ruth West, Arlene Jones, and Joan Purifoy; standing: Marion Thompson, Wayne Holt, and Louise Wingfield; gathered for meeting of the Allegheny Union Baptist Association
